  "body": "## ðŸŽ‰ Description\r\n- [  ] ðŸ› This is a bug report.\r\n- [x] ðŸ“ˆ This is a feature request.\r\n\r\n## ðŸ’» Environment\r\n\r\nNext, we need to know what your environment looks like.\r\n\r\n- OpenZeppelin 2.0 RC 1\r\n\r\n## ðŸ“ Details\r\n\r\nHola chicos!\r\nI really like the introduction of the Roles library.\r\nI've a couple of questions regarding it:\r\n\r\n1) Is there any specific reason why you did not added a Burner role? \r\nI'm thinking about some possibilities like having an ERC20 token acting as a kind of certificate of ownership so for e.g it can be minted and burned only by certain EOA or SC.\r\n\r\n2) I'm a bit confused about the _internal _removeMinter function_ e.g in the MinterRole.sol.\r\nI should extend it in the parent contract defining the rules for accessing to that function, right?\r\n\r\n3) Is reasonable secure that e.g in the Minter role minters can be added by other minters?\r\n\r\nThanks so much for your work guys.\r\n",
