    "body": "Thanks so much Nico for your time!\r\n1) I don't know if it is a good example but I was thinking about an ERC20 token project. \r\nHaving an amount of 10 token means that you own 10 of some off-chain asset kept safe by the token issuer.\r\nThe token act as a kind of certification.\r\nSo there is an actor that is the only one that can issue or burn that token.\r\nSo as far as you own that off-chain asset you have 10 of that token.\r\nFor redeem the off-chain asset you need to send to the issuer the 10 token.\r\nAt this point you redeem the off-chain asset and the issuer burns the 10 token.\r\n\r\nMaybe it is not an applicable example but It make me think about a Burnable role.\r\n\r\n2) Great it as I've intended it!\r\n\r\n3) The trust towards an EOA for example can change during times.\r\nMaybe before you (as manager / owner ) are able to remove that account as minter the already minter EAO start adding random minters just to screw up everything somehow.\r\n\r\nThanks again!\r\nA.",
