    "body": "Hey @andreafspeziale,\r\n\r\nThat first scenario does make sense, but it is supported by the current model :) You could burn your tokens and show that to the issuer, or transfer them to the issuer, and have they burn them.\r\n\r\nRegarding the minter role, transactions are non-reversible in the blockchain world, so you should be very careful as to who you give the role to. That said, if you wanted some sort of mechanism for one account to be able to remove others, you can easily do that by calling the internal `_remove` function.",
